# Figma Parity Sync Rule

When the user asks to "match", "sync", "reuse", or "apply same styles/tokens" from one module/component to others, use strict parity behavior.

## Source of Truth

- Treat the named source module as the single source of truth.
- Do not reinterpret styling semantically.
- Do not map to "closest" styles if exact source-bound values are available.

## Required Sync Scope

Mirror from source to targets for matching node roles:

1. Text styles and text color variable bindings
2. Container/input/button fills and stroke variable bindings
3. Spacing and radius variable bindings
4. Component usage parity (reuse documented component instances when source uses them)

## Completion Gate

Before finishing, provide a parity audit:

- `Matched`: list of node-role categories copied exactly
- `Mismatches`: any remaining differences from source (must be explicit)
- `Reason`: why mismatch exists (missing token/style/component, structural difference, API limit)

If any mismatch remains and no valid reason exists, continue iterating until parity is achieved.
